HEADWORD: Elcaja
<hw>El*ca"ja</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An Arabian tree (<spn>Trichilia emetica</spn>).
The fruit, which is emetic, is sometimes employed in the composition of
an ointment for the cure of the itch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

